    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix race condition in TRP information type response item comparison\n\n### Summary\nThe `eq_trp_info_type_response_item` function in `openair2/F1AP/lib/f1ap_positioning.c` was accessing a shared counter variable without proper synchronization, leading to race conditions when multiple threads called this function simultaneously.\n\nThis issue manifested as corrupted counter values and unpredictable behavior during positioning measurements. The problem was particularly evident during high-frequency TRP information processing where multiple threads would concurrently compare TRP information type response items.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/F1AP/lib/f1ap_positioning.c`: Added mutex locking around shared data access in `eq_trp_info_type_response_item` and related functions\n- `openair2/F1AP/lib/f1ap_positioning.h`: Updated function declarations\n- `CMakeLists.txt`: Added new positioning files to F1AP library build configuration\n- Created placeholder ASN.1 header files for TRP information type definitions\n\n"
}